.field
  = f.label :title
  %p Title to show on level pages (but not in level groups).
  = f.text_field :title
.field
  = render partial: 'levels/editors/checkboxes', locals: {f: f, field_name: :submittable, description: "Submittable"}
  %p
    If checked, students with teachers can "submit" a solution for
    grading. Submitting a solution means that it is marked as
    submitted and they can no longer edit it (unless a teacher returns
    it).
.field
  = render partial: 'levels/editors/checkboxes', locals: {f: f, field_name: :peer_reviewable, description: "Is peer reviewable"}
  %p
    If checked, students that submit a solution for grading can have their
    solution reviewed by peers.

.field
  = f.label :height
  %p Height of the answer textarea in px.
  = f.number_field :height, step: 50
.field
  = f.label :placeholder
  %p Placeholder text to show in the answer textarea.
  = f.text_field :placeholder
.field
  = f.label :solution
  %p Optional solution markdown to display to teachers.
  = f.text_area :solution, rows: 20
.field
  = render partial: 'levels/editors/checkboxes', locals: {f: f, field_name: :allow_user_uploads, description: "Allow User Uploads"}
  %p Let users upload files as solutions.
.field
  = render partial: 'levels/editors/checkboxes', locals: {f: f, field_name: :optional, description: "Optional"}
  %p If checked, an assessment page will still be considered complete even if this question is left blank.
